ysis can be extended to multi-product situations if a constant pre-determined sales mix is applied. If the assumption of a standard mix is relaxed, there will be no unique BEP.\"", "\"WEIGHTED AVERAGE C/S RATIO\":The weighted average C/S ratio, also known as the weighted average contribution to sales ratio, is a key metric used in multi-product breakeven analysis. It is calculated by taking the sum of the contribution to sales ratios of each product, weighted by their proportion of total sales. This ratio can be expressed through various formulas, such as:\n\n1. Weighted average C/S ratio = (Contribution margin of product X * Sales mix percentage of product X) + (Contribution margin of product Y * Sales mix percentage of product Y) + ...\n2. Weighted average C/S ratio = Budgeted total contribution / Budgeted total revenue.\n3. Weighted average C/S ratio = Total contribution (from all products) / Total revenue (from all products).\n\nThe weighted average C/S ratio is used to determine breakeven revenue and the sales revenue required to generate a target profit. For instance, a specific calculation example provided is $34.60 / $80, which equals 0.4325. Additionally, the weighted average contribution to sales ratio has been noted to be 87.06%.", "\"EXAMPLE OF MULTI-PRODUCT ANALYSIS\":\"Company A produces Product X and Y. The weighted average C/S ratio of 0.34375 or 34.375% is calculated by dividing the total contribution of X and Y by the total revenue of X and Y. BEP in sales revenue = Fixed costs/C/S ratio = $200,000/0.34375 = $581,819 sales revenue. To achieve a target profit of $300,000 = ($200,000 + $300,000)/0.34375 = $1,454,546.\"", "\"QUIZ: MULTI-PRODUCT ANALYSIS\":\"Pear manufactures laptop computers and smartphones. The quiz involves calculating the breakeven revenue and the sales revenue required to make a target profit of $245,000 using the weighted average C/S ratio.\"", "\"SALES MIX\":\"Sales mix is the ratio of different products sold by a company. It is important in multi-product CVP analysis.\"", "\"SALES REVENUE TO MAKE A PROFIT FORMULA\":\"Sales revenue to make a profit of $245,000 = (Fixed cost + Required profit) / Weighted average C/S ratio = (245,000 + 245,000) / 0.28 = $1,750,000\"", "\"SALES UNITS AT BREAKEVEN REVENUE\":\"In multi-product situations, breakeven revenue shows the total revenue required to break even, assuming the budgeted sales mix. Decision makers may wish to analyze this revenue by product. This can be estimated by multiplying the total breakeven revenue by the revenue ratio for each product.\"", "\"REVENUE RATIO FOR PRODUCT X\":\"Revenue ratio for product X = Budgeted revenue for product X / Total budgeted revenue\"", "\"REVENUE FROM PRODUCT X AT BREAKEVEN\":\"Revenue from product X = Total breakeven revenue * Revenue ratio for product X\"", "\"MULTI-PRODUCT PROFIT-VOLUME (PV) CHARTS\":\"In a multi-product environment, sales revenue is drawn on the horizontal axis (x axis) and profit is drawn on the vertical axis (y axis). Two approaches are taken to drawing the line denoting profit/loss: constant (fixed) sales mix; or ranking of products by profitability.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}